post_text:
The 2020 Canajoharie Yearbook is dedicated to Canajoharie Science Teacher, Patricia Prime, with a memorial of Canajoharie Middle School Math Teacher, Mrs. Michele DeLorenzo.

"On March 26, 2019, in the biology room, the whole right side of my body went numb, and Mrs. Prime knew exactly what to do. She kept me calm, and she was super worried for me and made sure I was safe until help arrived." ShellyAnn Hemmes, Canajoharie Student

"..Caring and committed teacher and colleague, invested in making math engaging, genuinely cared about our students, dedicated to being on the job
no matter how hard her days may have been. Endless strength to forge forward..hearts still ache with sadness forever in our hearts treasured memories will never disappear or fade." Lori Schaffer, Canajoharie Middle School English Teacher.

"..Caring and committed teacher and colleague, invested in making math engaging, genuinely cared about our students, dedicated to being on the job

post_text: Per Governor Cuomo's new executive order, the budget vote date has been extended to Tuesday, June 16th. To help facilitate the process, we will have a ballot box outside of the high school until Tuesday, June 9. All ballots after June 9 must be mailed in by Tuesday, June 16th at 5 pm. No additional ballots can be sent out after June 9. If anyone needs a ballot, please contact the district office at 518-673-6702 or email the District Clerk Andrea Muhlebeck and andrea.muhlebeck@canjo.org.

Montgomery County - NY
March 9 at 9:04 AM Â·

Montgomery County employees recently held a Jeans Day to assist the Canajoharie Central School District's Student Teacher Activity Rally.

STAR consists of faculty, staff and a committee of students who work to boost morale throughout the school through yearly themes and activities. This yearâ€™s theme, â€œRight Here. Right Nowâ€ conveys that instead of being focused on what happened yesterday or what could happen tomorrow, you are simply here, now.

The mission of the committee is to not only teach students academically, but to instill an aspiration to be good people, citizens, advocates and future adults. Funds will assist with the upcoming Canajoharie Game Show.

â€œWe are building bonds and lasting memories,â€ STAR Committee Advisor/ Business Education/CEIP, Co-Op Coordinator Tracy E. Evans said.

#MontgomeryCounty #MadeofSomethingStronger
#StrongerTogether #MondayMotivation #righthererightnow
